karen jusko the clayman institute for gender research skip to main content standford university the clayman institute for gender research the clayman institute for gender research home programs news strategic focus events about research fellowships library media center gender news no news found events no events found you are here home people karen jusko karen jusko assistant professor in department of political science school of humanities & sciences email kljusko stanford edu karen jusko is an assistant professor of political science at stanford university and a faculty affiliate of stanford's europe center and the center for the study of poverty and inequality she received her ph d in political science from the university of michigan in 2008 and has been an assistant professor at stanford university since 2007 jusko's research is motivated by questions about the origins of contemporary democratic politics in the us and in europe and has been supported by the national science foundation the european science foundation and the institute for research in the social sciences at stanford her current research is geared toward her upcoming book the political representation of the poor and focuses on questions such as how do electoral rules affect the poor when do parties have an incentive to seek the support of the low income citizens further information about karen jusko is available from her website donate make a donation social links facebook twitter youtube scribd contact serra house 589 capistrano way stanford ca 94305 8640 map 650 723 1994 gender email stanford edu
